{"questionId":"9075109","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>Two rockets, A and B, are moving towards each other on the same path. From the frame&nbsp;of reference of the Earth, an observer measures the speed of A to be 0.6<em>c</em> and the speed of&nbsp;B to be 0.4<em>c</em>. According to the observer on Earth, the distance between A and B is 6.0&nbsp;x 10<sup>8</sup> m.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><img src=\"__IMG__/d9f1f75c7e4f93c2d9997a199708bd92aa004aae.png\"></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Determine, according to an observer in A, the velocity of B.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\frac{{ - 0.4 - 0.6}}{{1 + 0.24}}\">\n  <mfrac>\n    <mrow>\n      <mo>−</mo>\n      <mn>0.4</mn>\n      <mo>−</mo>\n      <mn>0.6</mn>\n    </mrow>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>1</mn>\n      <mo>+</mo>\n      <mn>0.24</mn>\n    </mrow>\n  </mfrac>\n</math></span></p>\n<p>«–» 0.81<em>c</em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"9075109","referenceCode":"17N.3.SL.TZ0.5d","subjectId":"46-dp-physics-last-assessment-2024","title":"Determine, according to an observer in A, the velocity of B.","paper":"3","level":"SL","questionNumber":"d","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Option A: Relativity","Option A: Relativity","Option A: Relativity (Core topics)","A.2 – Lorentz transformations","Option A: Relativity","Option A: Relativity (Core topics)"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}